a(a^2 - 7)
a,k \in \mathbb{Z}, a(a^2 - 7) = 6k \\\text{Proof:}\\ a = 0 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 = 0 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 - 1\mod 6 = 5 \longrightarrow a(a^2 - 7) = 0\mod 6\\ a = 1 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 = 1 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 - 1\mod 6 = 0 \longrightarrow a(a^2 - 7) = 0\mod 6\\ a = 2 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 = 4 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 - 1\mod 6 = 3 \longrightarrow a(a^2 - 7) = 0\mod 6\\ a = 3 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 = 3 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 - 1\mod 6 = 2 \longrightarrow a(a^2 - 7) = 0\mod 6\\ a = 4 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 = 4 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 - 1\mod 6 = 3 \longrightarrow a(a^2 - 7) = 0\mod 6\\ a = 5 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 = 1 \mod 6 \longrightarrow a^2 - 1\mod 6 = 0 \longrightarrow a(a^2 - 7) = 0\mod 6\\ 
